<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>LockNest - Login</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>  
    <!-- Master Key Setup Section (shown after login/signup) -->
    <div class="container" id="masterKeySection">
        <div class="logo">
            <h1>🔐 LockNest</h1>
            <span>Secure · Fast · Reliable</span>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
            <h2 style="color: #2d2d3a; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 12px;">🔑 Create Your Master Key</h2>
            <p style="color: #8888a0; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6;">
                Your master key is the <strong style="color: #e74c3c;">single most important</strong> credential in this vault.
                You will need it every time you want to reveal a saved password.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Warnings & Guidelines -->
        <div class="master-key-warnings">
            <div class="warning-item warning-critical">
                <span class="warning-icon">⚠️</span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Write it down!</strong>
                    <p>If you forget your master key, there is NO way to recover it or your saved passwords.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="warning-item warning-important">
                <span class="warning-icon">📝</span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Store it safely</strong>
                    <p>Keep it in a password manager or a secure physical location. Do not share it with anyone.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="warning-item warning-tip">
                <span class="warning-icon">🔒</span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Make it strong</strong>
                    <p>Use a long, unique phrase that you'll remember but others can't guess. Avoid common words or personal info.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="warning-item warning-tip">
                <span class="warning-icon">❌</span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Don't reuse passwords</strong>
                    <p>Your master key should not be the same as any password you store in this vault.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Master Key Form -->
        <form action = "/auth/createdkey" method="post" style="margin-top: 24px;">
                <%- include('partials/errorMessage') %>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="newMasterKey">Enter Master Key</label>
                <input type="password" name="masterKey" id="newMasterKey" placeholder="Create a strong master key" required minlength="6">
            </div>
            <div class="form-group">
                <label for="confirmMasterKey">Confirm Master Key</label>
                <input type="password" name="confirmMasterKey" id="confirmMasterKey" placeholder="Re-enter your master key" required minlength="6">
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">💾 Save & Continue</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>